Very simple compiled programming language

Name - Undecided

GOALS:
    - Parser and tokenizer libraries
        - STB-style?
    - Register optimization pass?
        - My previous compiled languages didn't really have this
    - NO chance of memory leaks
        - I usually don't check every scenario because I'm more interested in the code, but no matter how long this takes, this programming language needs to be memory-safe.
            - UPDATE: This current version certainly compromises memory-wise, there are a bunch of memory leak spots, but I'll make it work and then make it work safely

Maybe README.md format coming up soon?
    I'm still pretty new to READMEs, might take some time

HOW IT WORKS (more will be added as I develop this language):
    - Tokenizer library
        - Maybe add macros for creating the tokenizer?
        - There might be some drawbacks to using macros in approach, but I want to support as diverse of a range for programming languages as possible
    - Parser / AST library
        - Might be the hardest one: there are a lot of programming styles for ASTS
            - I'm probably going to compromise and make it work on some minimal styles -- I might add more later, but for now, that could do
